Rating: 4
Ever have a mental lapse in the kitchen? Then maybe you'll sympathize. I've never worked with porcini mushrooms before, and just barely averted disaster. Even though they are dried, do RINSE them prior to soaking in the hot water. I had skipped that critical step, and when I tasted a softened mushroom, my mouth was full of grit! A good rinse in the strainer took care of that problem, and then I poured the reserved liquid through a paper towel (as I should have done before) to catch any remaining grit. All the effort was worth it. The porcinis release a gorgeous earthy, foresty aroma that is unlike any other mushroom I've had. The fragrance and flavor of the final ragu was a treat.

