This was superb. I doubled the recipe but only added 2 cans of broth. I did not wait for the sauce to periodically reduce. Rather, I just added everything and let it cook for 3 hours. It was thick, but not too thick. We waited until the next day to eat it (with really high quality imported fettucini) -- worth the wait to let the flavors develop. YUM!!

Rating: 3
I love this ragu. I have made it several times and now only double it. It is best a day or so later and freezes well. For casual entertaining with salad, bread and wine, or simply to grab a quick bite. A definite winner for kids and adults which has become a regular dish in our family.

Rating: 4
My husband and I made this last weekend and loved it. It as even better two nights later after the flavors blended.

Rating: 4
